  "prompt": "Does all the questions get answered in Quora?",
  "response": "No, not all questions get answered on Quora. While Quora is a platform where users can ask questions and receive answers from a wide range of people, including experts and enthusiasts, there are several reasons why some questions may remain unanswered:\n\n1. **Complexity or Specificity**: Some questions are very complex, technical, or niche, making it difficult for anyone with the right knowledge to come across them and provide an answer.\n\n2. **Popularity**: Questions that gain more visibility due to upvotes, shares, or being asked by popular users are more likely to be answered. Less popular or obscure questions may not attract enough attention.\n\n3. **Quality of the Question**: Poorly worded, vague, or unclear questions may discourage users from answering. Questions that are too broad or subjective might also be challenging to answer.\n\n4. **Lack of Expertise**: If a question requires specialized knowledge, and no one with that expertise sees it, it may go unanswered.\n\n5. **Time Constraints**: Active users may not have the time to answer every question they come across, especially if they are already answering many others.\n\n6. **Interest**: Some questions may not be interesting or engaging enough to motivate users to respond.\n\n7. **Policy Violations**: Questions that violate Quora\u2019s policies or guidelines may be removed or restricted, leading to no answers.\n\nQuora does have mechanisms to help increase the chances of getting an answer, such as suggesting questions to relevant users or notifying those who have expertise in the topic. However, it\u2019s still not guaranteed that every question will be answered.",
